        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add JSON-RPC plugin bindings",
        "body": "Closes #98004\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw plugin authors who want to implement runtime logic in Rust, Python, Go, or another non-TypeScript language currently need to handroll process bridges behind each plugin surface. That duplicates stdio framing, lifecycle cleanup, timeout handling, environment inheritance policy, HTTP body handling, and Gateway response mapping across plugins.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds a public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin` entrypoint with `defineJsonRpcPluginEntry`. The TypeScript entry remains the synchronous source of truth for OpenClaw plugin descriptors, while invoked tool, hook, HTTP route, and Gateway method calls dispatch to a lazily started child process over newline-framed JSON-RPC 2.0 on stdio. The implementation keeps existing OpenClaw auth/scope gates at the registered host surface and avoids introducing a socket listener.\n\n## User Impact\n\nPlugin authors can now build language-agnostic plugin runtimes while still using OpenClaw's existing plugin architecture and manifest model. Rust or other native runtimes only need a small JavaScript descriptor file plus a JSON-RPC stdio server.\n\nAI-assisted: yes. I understand the code change and validated the touched SDK boundary.\n\n## Evidence\n\nCurrent focused proof on `d7c92b53c1fb645a23b9873d116bceb4fbfae7e5`:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.process.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.ts src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.process.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nEarlier full SDK/docs proof on this branch also passed:\n\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:surface:check`\n- `pnpm check:docs`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:src`\n- `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:check-exports`\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n\nImplementation size: 13 files changed, +1793/-7 total. Public runtime code is one new SDK helper (`src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.ts`, 750 LOC) plus focused tests (`src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.test.ts`, 584 LOC; `src/plugin-sdk/json-rpc-plugin.process.test.ts`, 332 LOC); the rest is export metadata, API/surface/docs generated metadata, and docs.\n",
        "branch": "codex/json-rpc-plugin-bindings",
